Prince Alwaleed Bin Talal has pledged to give 100 Bentleys to Saudi pilots involved in Yemen air strikes . 
  He is the Saudi King Abdullah's nephew and owns $300 million stake in Twitter . 
  Saudi Arabian forces launched air strikes a month ago to stop Houthi rebels advancing . 
  They pledged on Tuesday that the raids would stop but they appeared to resume on Wednesday . 
  Prince has promised to give each of the 100 pilots a free Bentley . 
 